==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Synchronism
<hw>Syn"chro*nism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/, fr.
<?/ to be contemporary with, from <?/ synchronous. See
<er>Synchronous</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The concurrence of events
in time; simultaneousness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The tabular arrangement of historical events and
personages, according to their dates.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Paint.)</fld> <def>A representation, in the same
picture, of two or events which occured at different times.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Synchronistic</ent>⟦br⟧
